<p class="page" id="a7661039">[Page 39]</p>
<p>censorship regulations are things to be ignored.  Cecil came to Alexandria to see me after my first return from Gallipoli &amp; he then had heard from you but I've not seen him since altho I heard of him from Genl. Holmes in whose command he was &amp; who told me that he had recommended him for some distinction.  I was hardly as unlucky as from your letter you think I had been as I was at both the landing and the evacuation having left the unit I came with &amp; taken a Battery at Anzac.  My experiences so far have taught me a lot, first that one wants to be either a General or very young to stand any length of time on active service, secondly there are Generals who are those (many) who are not.</p>
